    <note>Lu(5) Zhen [3634] Lu Dian, WJ, 15.13a-14b (wife, born Wu, who died in 1091 at age 86 and who may be related to the other Jianning Wu), 16.15a-16a (concubine, a Shaoxing, Shanyin county born Zhou, who became his consort at age 26 and died in 1070 at age 65); Kuaiji xu, 6.2b. Since born Zhou's funerary inscription notes that the legal wife died in Huangyou (1049-53), born Wu(3) must have been wife #2, who married him no younger than age 44! There may be mis-identifications here since CBD does not cite born Zhou as a wife or consort of Zhen, but also provides no alternative. Aoyama identifies her as a wife of Zhen. Internal evidence inconclusive, although her sons have the same generational names as those of Zhen and she may, in fact, be a consort of one of Zhen's brothers. CBD, 3, 2656.</note>
